node.text:
Here is a little summary of this month's Patreon Rewards 💕 Two voice over lessons about drawing clothes, traditional and digital paintings with explained process steps, videos, files, tools, brushes wallpapers and more 🥰 If you still want to join you have time until 31st July 10pm PST! (around 2 days) 🌸☺️🌸
More info in my latest patreon post → patreon.com/ladowska

Once again, thank you so much for everyone's support. 🤗💕

node.text: A little gift I managed to craft in my moving madness as I got to visit Too offices in Tokyo today - the company that makes Copic Markers which had incredible influence on my career up to this day. Thank you for having me @copic_official 😭🌸 I was super stressed but it ended up so nice and everybody was so friendly and welcoming. I will post a picture with a Copic marker bigger than me on my photo account 😉

node.text: [Contest!] Calpico has just announced a package design contest for their new flavor Calpico Melon🍈! I'm excited to share my illustration for the contest (swipe→ to see it in full!) You have a chance of YOUR artwork becoming the official limited-time packaging for Melon Calpico all over the world next summer - don't miss your chance ;) The official design theme is "Fun & Lively, Young and Contemporary, Positive and Upbeat" 💛☺️💚 To join, you can download the template, create your design, and submit it! Make sure to check their official rules at @calpico.usa and in my stories 🎀🌸💕

node.text:
This month's Patreon voice-over lesson will be about drawing hair as requested! :)

I talk about as many tips, dos, don'ts and techniques on how to make hair look natural and cool, so hopefully there'll be something for everybody regardless of skill level.
Hope you'll like it 💕 

Voice-over will be included in Aoi and Momoiro tiers with other rewards! Sign up ends soon, on the 30th June 10pm PST.

node.text:
Friends 💗
A drawing from September last year. It was my first drawing on a challenge to start drawing full body poses and not just headshots and I have filled in 4 sketchbooks so far. I haven't posted much from those online, maybe one day I'll compile it in a sketchbook of some sort 😊 maybe. This one may be full of flaws that I feel I could do better today, but it holds a special place in my heart as the first step on this journey ☺️

Here's a better picture of my new character, Rin! 🥰 Happy and colorful girl to make everyone's day a better day ☺️ If you're sad and need to cheer up draw Rin in your style and post to #SketchWithAsiaRin - happiness guaranteed 😉😉😉 there is no deadline since there is no deadline to happiness, I will share some entries from time to time 🥰
🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈🌈
